'''契诃夫之枪'''（{{lang-ru|Чеховское ружьё}}），又译'''契诃夫法则'''，是一种[[叙事学|叙事手法]]，该手法认为故事中提及的每一个元素都应在后文出场，不然就没有必要提及。该手法常见于[[戏剧|戏剧]]中<ref name="Leeds1">{{cite web |author1=[[利兹大学|Leeds University]] |title=Uncle Vanya at Pyramid Theatre – An Anglicised Triumph of Russian Theatre |url=https://www.thegryphon.co.uk/2019/03/24/uncle-vanya-at-pyramid-theatre-an-anglicised-triumph-of-russian-theatre/ |website=Leeds University |publisher=Leeds University |accessdate=2020-07-19 |archive-date=2020-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718214149/https://www.thegryphon.co.uk/2019/03/24/uncle-vanya-at-pyramid-theatre-an-anglicised-triumph-of-russian-theatre/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该手法因俄國小說家[[安东·帕夫洛维奇·契诃夫|安东·契诃夫]]多次在与人来往的信件中提及而逐渐知名<ref name="marble" />。

== 概述 ==
契诃夫之枪最早是一种戏剧手法，揭示了故事早期引入故事的元素在故事后期的重要性。

目前学界主流意见认为契诃夫之枪最早出现在[[安东·契诃夫|契诃夫]]本人的戏剧《{{tsl|en|Uncle_Vanya|万尼亚舅舅}}》的第四幕中<ref>{{cite book|author1=Jessica Hinds-Bond|editor=Douglas Clayton, Yana Meerzon|title=Adapting Chekhov: The Text and Its Mutations.|date=2014|publisher=[[剑桥大学出版社|剑桥大学出版社]]|location=Cambridge University|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/theatre-research-international/article/adapting-chekhov-the-text-and-its-mutations-edited-by-j-douglas-clayton-and-yana-meerzon-new-york-routledge-2013-pp-xviii-316-90130-hb/8CDF72062EE9A6454587AAC9D33E631D|accessdate=2020-07-19|last=|first=|year=|isbn=|pages=|archive-date=2018-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615213205/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/theatre-research-international/article/adapting-chekhov-the-text-and-its-mutations-edited-by-j-douglas-clayton-and-yana-meerzon-new-york-routledge-2013-pp-xviii-316-90130-hb/8CDF72062EE9A6454587AAC9D33E631D|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Leeds1" />。不过也有人不认同这种说法，并认为《万尼亚舅舅》中的转折太短不构成契诃夫之枪。

今日，该手法已经不再仅仅用于戏剧，同样出现在小说、故事等文学作品中，成为了一种文学手法。

==契诃夫提出的法则原型==
契诃夫曾在与友人的信件中多次提到这一手法：<ref>{{citation|title=Chekhov's art, a stylistic analysis|author=Petr Mikhaĭlovich Bit︠s︡illi|year=1983|publisher=Ardis|page=x}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=The Literature 100: A Ranking of the Most Influential Novelists, Playwrights, and Poets of All Time|author=Daniel S. Burt|year=2008|publisher=Infobase Publishing}}</ref><ref name="marble">{{citation|title=Chekhov: The Silent Voice of Freedom|author=Valentine T. Bill|year=1987|publisher=Philosophical Library}}</ref>
*“请将一切与故事无关的事物都从故事中移除。如果你说第一幕中有把枪挂在墙上，那么在第二幕或者第三幕中这把枪必须发射，不然就没必要挂在那。”<ref name="marble" /><ref>{{cite journal|date=1911|title=Из воспоминаний об А.П. Чехове|trans-title=Memoirs|url=|journal=Русская Мысль [Russian Thought]|volume=|page=44|via=|author=С.Н. Щукин [Sergius Shchukin]}}</ref>
* 摘自契诃夫与亚历山大·拉扎列夫的信件来往：“如果一把装满子弹的枪不开火，就不要把它放在舞台上——正如如果不遵守诺言就不要允诺。”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://berlin.wolf.ox.ac.uk/lists/quotations/quotations_by_ib.html|title=Quotations by Berlin|work=ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2020-07-15|archive-date=2018-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701005628/http://berlin.wolf.ox.ac.uk/lists/quotations/quotations_by_ib.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=http://chehov.niv.ru/chehov/letters/1888-1889/letter-707.htm|author=Чехов А. П.|title=Чехов — Лазареву (Грузинскому) А. С.|date=1889-11-01|work=Чехов А. П. Полное собрание сочинений и писем|publisher=АН СССР. Ин-т мировой лит.|accessdate=2020-07-19|archive-date=2017-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113124929/http://chehov.niv.ru/chehov/letters/1888-1889/letter-707.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Russian Literature in the Nineteenth Century: Essays|page=163|year=1976|publisher=Magnes Press, [[耶路撒冷希伯来大学|耶路撒冷希伯来大学]]|author={{tsl|en|Leah Goldberg|利亚·戈尔德贝格|Leah Goldberg}}}}</ref>。
* 摘自 《戏剧与艺术》1904年7月第28期：《契诃夫回忆录》：“第一幕挂在墙上的枪，第二幕中一定会发射。不然这把枪就没必要挂在那。”<ref>In 1889, 24-year-old Ilia Gurliand noted these words down from Chekhov's conversation: "If in Act I you have a pistol hanging on the wall, then it must fire in the last act". Donald Rayfield, ''Anton Chekhov: A Life'', New York: Henry Holt and Company, 1997, {{ISBN|0-8050-5747-1}}, 203. Ernest. J. Simmons says that Chekhov repeated the point later (which may account for the variations). Ernest J. Simmons, ''Chekhov: A Biography'', Chicago: [[芝加哥大學出版社|芝加哥大學出版社]], 1962, {{ISBN|0-226-75805-2}}, 190.</ref>

== 反响 ==
[[欧内斯特·海明威|欧内斯特·海明威]]曾讥讽部分英文作家对这一法则的过度追捧：他的一篇文章《小故事的艺术》提及，他在一篇短文《{{tsl|en|Fifty Grand|五万大洋}}》曾一开场就介绍了两个角色，但再也没在故事中出场过。海明威认为细节的确重要，但同时认为读者不必深究每个细节的意义<ref>{{citation|url=https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/9656160.pdf|author=Adrian c Hunter|date=1999|title=Complete with missing parts": modernist short fiction as interrogative text|pp=126–127, 201–203|accessdate=2020-07-15|archive-date=2017-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171209144910/https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/9656160.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

后来的部分作家进一步认为，契诃夫之枪的关键在于对于被提及的“枪”应用一定的手法暗示其重要性<ref>{{cite web |author1=nownovel |title=Chekhov’s Gun: What it is and how to use it like a pro |url=https://www.nownovel.com/blog/use-chekhovs-gun/ |website=nownovel |accessdate=2020-07-19 |archive-date=2021-02-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214205453/https://www.nownovel.com/blog/use-chekhovs-gun/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

